item.title: What's the game called?
item.dc:creator: CPU
item.description:
Mabilis:

hmm I also have a game in my mind I always google but cannot find.

It is a snowboarding game on an old console… ps1 maybe? maybe the gamecube? I’m not sure I played it at a friends house loads when I was little.

Basically the main mode you were racing the other snowboarders, I think you could choose your snowboard (I remember a purple… alpine snowboard, was very fast I always chose it). And when you press down/backwards it made you faster.
You also got points for doing tricks like backflips, you could press left and down to do some amazing trick but it was difficult to land it and get the points… Also, there was a track called half pipe and the goal was to do the best tricks get the most points).

SSX or SSX Trickery?
